<br>
The druid and I have the place done fairly well. One thing to remember, the elementals ALL roam, they all have a 1-3 minute spawn time it seems, you will NEVER be able to clear the island, it will ALWAYS be filled to the rim. The only way to clear the place is to bassically raid it with a large guild.<br>
<br>
Yes, you can take it at 25, I have a partner which makes it easier though. What you do is mem your expell summoned (I think) and cancel magic (for the fire elementals). It will be fairly hard for you, but you should be able to solo one at a time.<br>
<br>
As an added bonus, this is the zone in which you can buy your summon armor line and your elemental defender spell. <br>
<br>
ALL THE ARMOR SPELLS AND THE DEFENDER SPELL were 2pp. EVEN THE PLATE ARMOR SPELL. The vendor is by the portal (right down the stairs). The REALLY odd thing is that he buys no drop things, I have yet to test summond thing, but I susspect he will buy those too. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=yomad>YoMaD</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#333333>(3/31/02 8:44:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Yes, I got here at 25</span><hr size=1> Well I'm currently leveling in Marus Seru, staying there until 29. Maybe at 29 I'll go for the elementals since it will be easier then. <p><img src="http://yomad.freewebspace.com/YoMaDsig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=eriol>Eriol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(4/1/02 6:23:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Way to Twilight</span><hr size=1> The way that I went was Nexus, Shadow Haven, Paludal Caverns, Hollowshade Moor, Grimling Forest, Tenebrous Mountains, Katta Castellum, Twilight Sea.  The most dangerous part of the whole journey was Tenebrous.  Have to watch out for the bats on the mountians.  Otherwise, that zone is easy with invisi.  Just get a SoW before you port up, or get one in Shar Vahl (right off of Hollowshade).  Wasn't a big problem, and not TOO dangerous.  Once you are in Katta, just bind there, and you have a good bank spot too.<br>
<br>
For all those going to Katta, remember in the caster guild, that the &quot;banner&quot; on the back wall is a teleporter.  Just go beneath it, and touch it to move between the lvls.  3rd lvl is one with trainer and spells.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps everyone trying to get to Twilight.<br>
